== unsigned overflow is rejected by number parsing:
shit: 1:14: error: --runs expects a number, got '18446744073709551616'.
== invalid values carry granular carets:
shit: 1:14: error: --runs expects a number, got 'nope'.
     1 |  bench --runs nope true
       |               ^~~~ here.
shit: 1:14: error: --runs expects a number, got 'nope'.
     1 |  bench --runs=nope true
       |               ^~~~ here.
shit: 1:14: error: --runs expects a number from 1 through 100000.
     1 |  bench --runs 0 true
       |               ^~ here.
shit: 1:18: error: --duration is too large.
     1 |  bench --duration 18446744073710 true
       |                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~ here.
shit: 1:7: error: --runs expects a number, got 'nope'.
     1 |  bench "--runs=nope" true
       |        ^~~~~~~~~~~~~ here.
shit: 1:18: error: --runs expects a number, got 'nope'.
     1 |  runs=nope; bench --runs=$runs true
       |                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~ here.
== an overflowing duration is rejected:
rc=1
